This paper deals with knowledge graph completion, which is a task related to artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI). The proposed model, TuckER, is a linear model based on tensor decomposition, which is a common technique in machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the performance of TuckER on standard link prediction datasets, which are commonly used in database research (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper deals with inferring missing facts based on existing ones, which is a task related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
